Aim:
To write a C++ program to display student details using class and objects.

Algorithm:
Start
Create a class Student with data members: name, roll, department.
Define a function to get input and another to display output.
Create object for the class.
Call functions using object.
Display student information.
Stop.

Program:
#include<iostream>
using namespace std;

class Student {
    string name, dept;
    int roll;
public:
    void getData() {
        cout<<"Enter Name: ";
        cin>>name;
        cout<<"Enter Roll Number: ";
        cin>>roll;
        cout<<"Enter Department: ";
        cin>>dept;
    }

    void display() {
        cout<<"\n--- Student Details ---\n";
        cout<<"Name: "<<name<<endl;
        cout<<"Roll Number: "<<roll<<endl;
        cout<<"Department: "<<dept<<endl;
    }
};

int main() {
    Student s;
    s.getData();
    s.display();
    return 0;
}

Sample Output:

Enter Name: Rahul
Enter Roll Number: 101
Enter Department: CSE
--- Student Details ---
Name: Rahul
Roll Number: 101
Department: CSE

Result:
The program successfully displays student information using class and objects.
The program successfully displays student information using class and objects.
